00:00:17.220 --> 00:00:18.160
9.

00:00:18.160 --> 00:00:22.820
Çatalhöyük, Turkey
Built in what was once Mesopotamia, the city

00:00:22.820 --> 00:00:28.270
of Çatalhöyük, which now resides in Turkey,
is easily one of the biggest mysteries of

00:00:28.270 --> 00:00:29.540
the ancient world.

00:00:29.540 --> 00:00:35.219
I mean reaaaallly ancient, it reached its
heyday around 7000 BC!!

00:00:35.219 --> 00:00:37.649
This place makes ancient Rome look modern!!

00:00:37.649 --> 00:00:42.179
These tightly clustered mudbrick houses kind
of look like honeycombs, don’t you think?

00:00:42.179 --> 00:00:46.789
Every single house in this city shares a wall
or two with another house, just like how honeycomb

00:00:46.789 --> 00:00:48.159
is connected in a hive.

00:00:48.159 --> 00:00:52.410
To get out of their houses, the people would
use ladders and cut doors in the roofs.

00:00:52.410 --> 00:00:56.430
The people would actually walk across the
roofs like we would walk across the street.

00:00:56.430 --> 00:01:00.859
The Neolithic residents left behind paintings,
plaster reliefs, and pottery.

00:01:00.859 --> 00:01:03.479
As well as their dead which they buried in
the floors!

00:01:03.479 --> 00:01:08.610
At one time, this thriving ancient metropolis
had about 8,000 residents and archaeologists

00:01:08.610 --> 00:01:12.170
are still uncovering thousands of mysterious
objects.

00:01:12.170 --> 00:01:15.980
There are many skulls found that have the
same type of head wounds in the skulls that

00:01:15.980 --> 00:01:18.830
later healed (so they were non fatal).

00:01:18.830 --> 00:01:23.040
This has led archaeologists to believe that
they might have been an egalitarian society

00:01:23.040 --> 00:01:26.800
but that they used controlled violence to
keep everyone in check.

00:01:26.800 --> 00:01:31.440
We are still trying to understand how these
people lived, and why things eventually fell

00:01:31.440 --> 00:01:32.440
apart.

00:01:32.440 --> 00:01:33.440
8.

00:01:33.440 --> 00:01:37.550
Palenque, Mexico
Mexico is a land of many mysteries and lost

00:01:37.550 --> 00:01:38.690
people and cities.

00:01:38.690 --> 00:01:42.930
But easily the biggest civilization, with
the biggest mystery surrounding them, are

00:01:42.930 --> 00:01:44.050
the Mayans.

00:01:44.050 --> 00:01:48.740
This tribe came from an unknown area, arrived
in Mexico, and set up an empire that lasted

00:01:48.740 --> 00:01:50.940
over 3000 years.

00:01:50.940 --> 00:01:52.100
Then they were gone.

00:01:52.100 --> 00:01:56.960
To this day, many still study the Mayans in
order to find out more about them, and especially

00:01:56.960 --> 00:01:58.450
what happened to them.

00:01:58.450 --> 00:02:01.860
One of their most well-preserved cities that
they made was Palenque.

00:02:01.860 --> 00:02:07.170
Palenque is a prime example of how well the
Mayans could plan and construct their cities.

00:02:07.170 --> 00:02:12.020
This place not only had temples, but other
massive public and ceremonial buildings, and

00:02:12.020 --> 00:02:16.499
texts inscribed in various places that help
tell the tales of the empire.

00:02:16.499 --> 00:02:21.769
So here's the question, if the Mayans were
so powerful, and Palenque was so advanced,

00:02:21.769 --> 00:02:23.549
why did they abandon it?

00:02:23.549 --> 00:02:27.989
Most historians note that the city was abandoned
around the 1400's, much like various other

00:02:27.989 --> 00:02:29.079
Mayan cities.

00:02:29.079 --> 00:02:30.150
But why?

00:02:30.150 --> 00:02:31.989
Why did they leave such wonders behind?

00:02:31.989 --> 00:02:33.269
Were they driven out?

00:02:33.269 --> 00:02:34.999
Did they have to flee to survive?

00:02:34.999 --> 00:02:37.659
Or were they all affected by a disease?

00:02:37.659 --> 00:02:41.459
No one knows the answers to these questions,
but there are many expeditions going on to

00:02:41.459 --> 00:02:43.629
try and figure out the answer.

